      "reason": "Headings that are part of the reader‑facing content must be translated, but the original English heading is a proper noun and should remain unchanged."
    },
    {
      "priority": "high",
      "match": "## Tabla de Contenidos Visual\n<div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n  [![](../breach-infographic-blueprint.svg)](../breach-infographic-blueprint.svg)\n  [![](../breach-infographic-response.svg)](../breach-infographic-response.svg)\n</div>",
      "replacement": "## Visual Table Of Contents\n\n![Blueprint for defending against supply chain attacks, with six steps: 1. Isolate (run inside DevContainers or cloud environments), 2. Limit Mounts (never mount Home, ~/.ssh, ~/.aws, etc.), 3. Scope Secrets (expose only necessary credentials), 4. Tripwire (seed canaries in .env files, ~/.aws/config, CI/CD, Password Managers), 5. Delay Risk (delay package updates 1+ day with pnpm's minimumReleaseAge), and 6. Respond Fast (rotate keys, passwords, communicate, monitor).](./breach-infographic-blueprint.svg)",
      "reason": "The source includes a single infographic with a detailed alt‑text; the candidate replaced it with a generic grid and omitted the alt description, breaking accessibility and MDX fidelity."
    },
    {
      "priority": "high",
      "match": "## El Problema: Humanos como Tráfico\nLos humanos no son límites. Los humanos son tráfico. En un mundo de ataques impulsados por IA, su laptop es el premio mayor.",
      "replacement": "## The \"Be Careful\" Non-Solution\n\n\"Be careful\" is weak advice. It asks the human to be the boundary.\n\nHumans are not boundaries. Humans are traffic.\n\nBoundaries are boring: filesystem isolation, encrypted‑at‑rest secrets, short‑lived credentials, hardware‑backed auth, and alerts that fire the moment a fake secret gets touched.",
      "reason": "The candidate rewrote this entire section, losing the original nuance and technical framing; the translation must preserve the source meaning."
    },
    {
      "priority": "high",
      "match": "## Solución: Dev Containers y Canarytokens\nAl usar Dev Containers, aislamos las herramientas de desarrollo. Al usar Canarytokens, detectamos la brecha en segundos.\n\n```json\n// .devcontainer/devcontainer.json\n{\n  \"name\": \"Secure Environment\",\n  \"features\": {\n    \"ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/sshd:1\": {}\n  }\n}\n```",
      "replacement": "## Dev Containers — By Default\n\n[Development Containers](https://github.com/devcontainers/spec) are the single highest‑leverage change most teams aren't doing. A Dev Container runs project work inside an isolated Docker container. `npm install`, `pip install`, `postinstall` scripts, AI shell commands, VS Code extensions — all of it happens in a 'workspace' or container that cannot see the rest of your machine.\n\n<p class=\"inset\">Ask Claude Code to setup DevContainers in any project.</p>\n\n```jsonc\n// .devcontainer/devcontainer.json\n{\n  \"name\": \"app\",\n  \"image\": \"mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/typescript-node:1-22\",\n  \"mounts\": [\n    \"source=${localWorkspaceFolder},target=/workspaces/app,type=bind,consistency=cached\"\n  ]\n}\n```",
      "reason": "The source code snippet and surrounding explanatory text are essential for technical accuracy; the candidate's snippet is unrelated and omits critical instructions."
    },
    {
      "priority": "high",
      "match": "## Conclusión\nLa seguridad no es un estado, es un proceso de respuesta rápida.",
      "replacement": "## You Have Minutes\n\nWhen a canary fires — or GitHub alerts you that a token was used from an unexpected IP — you have a window. Minutes, maybe a few hours. Not a week.\n\n- **Rotate first, investigate later.** Revoke tokens before you understand what happened.\n- **Check for attacker persistence.** New OAuth apps, IAM users, deploy keys, API tokens created before they left.\n- **Kill active browser sessions.** Force logout on everything you care about.\n- **Tell someone.** Security incidents improve with witnesses and timestamps.",
      "reason": "The candidate truncated the final actionable checklist, removing essential incident‑response steps."
    },
    {
      "priority": "high",
      "match": "## Sources and Useful Reading\n- [Verizon 2026 DBIR overview](https://www.verizon.com/business/resources/reports/dbir/)\n- ... (list truncated)",
      "replacement": "## Sources and Useful Reading\n\n- [Verizon 2026 DBIR overview](https://www.verizon.com/business/resources/reports/dbir/)\n- [Mandiant: UNC5537 Targets Snowflake Customer Instances](https://cloud.google.com/blog/topics/threat-intelligence/unc5537-snowflake-data-theft-extortion)\n- [Microsoft: Lumma Stealer delivery techniques and capabilities](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2025/05/21/lumma-stealer-breaking-down-the-delivery-techniques-and-capabilities-of-a-prolific-infostealer/)\n- [Microsoft DCU: Disrupting Lumma Stealer](https://blogs.microsoft.com/on-the-issues/2025/05/21/microsoft-leads-global-action-against-favored-cybercrime-tool/)\n- [GitHub: Security hardening for GitHub Actions](https://docs.github.com/en/actions/security-for-github-actions/security-guides/security-hardening-for-github-actions)\n- [Development Containers specification](https://github.com/devcontainers/spec)\n- [Thinkst Canarytokens overview](https://help.canary.tools/hc/en-gb/articles/10905485310109-Canarytoken-Overview-and-Use-Cases)\n- [Canarytokens.org (free, open source)](https://canarytokens.org)\n- [Socket.dev supply chain security](https://socket.dev)\n- [Snyk](https://snyk.io)\n- [Wiz](https://wiz.io)\n- [Objective-See LuLu](https://objective-see.org/products/lulu.html)\n- [Little Snitch](https://obdev.at/products/littlesnitch/)\n- [Claude Code permissions](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/permissions)",
      "reason": "The source article includes a comprehensive list of references; the candidate omitted most of them, reducing credibility and breaking the expected structure."
    }
  ],
  "rationale": "The candidate is a severely truncated, loosely paraphrased version that loses the majority of the source content, breaks MDX structure, and alters key metadata. Technical accuracy and cultural fidelity are low, and many high‑priority fixes are required.",
  "publishReady": false
}

